		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Nashville</placeName> <date>Novr 28&#44; 5619</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I spoke last night with <persName>Mr.<lb/> Nathan</persName>&#44; he told me&#44; that he had not yet recd your Oc&#61;<lb/>cident which is indeed more than two months that I<lb/> wrote to you.  I informed you there every thing you wrote<lb/> to me&#44; I am very sorry if this should be the case.<lb/>  Did <persName>Mr. L Powers</persName> write to you&#63; <sic>as</sic> he promised me<lb/> <persName>Mr. Garriston</persName>&#44; desires his account&#44; and will send you money.<lb/>  From <persName>Mr Wolf</persName> I can get no reply so as to answer you<lb/> I think the best is either you should write to him<lb/> direct&#44; or enclosed a few words to him in a letter to<lb/> me&#44; and there I will do what I can for you.<lb/>  Please send your Occident or this direction</p>
				<p><persName>Mr. S. Nathan</persName>&#44; <placeName>Nashville Tenn.</placeName></p>
				<p>I have much to write&#44; but I will do it some other<lb/> time please God.  I remain your most obedient and<lb/> truly servt</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">E Marcus</persName></p>
		</body>
